<font color="#FF0000">HEALING TIME</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 12  0:58:53 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
 It is strange, that after all these many years some <br>
people still condemn a war and forget those that fought<br>
and died there.<br><br>
 Can we not forget whether the war was right or wrong<br>
and finally mourn in peace for those that were lost and<br>
those that still suffer their wounds in silent pain.<br><br>
 Those that went, answered the call, and should be<br>
admired and respected.<br><br>
 The war is over, let the politics end and the true<br>
healing begin.<br><br>
 This is a very special site and I hope you continue with<br>
what you are trying to do here.<br><br>
 
<p><code>-- ptut@netins.net  (Earl D. Tuttle) </code><p>


